  <a href="#1" id="1">
   MINORITIES AND MOLDOVAN
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   A CEASEFIRE in Moldova was threatened on Mar. 5, 1992 when a truck driver transporting militiamen was shot dead by machinegun fire in the self-proclaimed Trans Dnestr republic, home of the Russian-speaking minority.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The shooting came shortly after the ceasefire came into effect between the Moldovan authorities, dominated by ethnic Romanians, and the minority based in the republic on the east bank of the river Dnestr.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Ukrainians and Russians together represent some 27 per cent of the population, with Moldovans accounting for 64 per cent.
  </a>
